<%= content_for :body_id, 'home' %>

<div id="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="hero-text animated fadeInDown">
      Tired of manual tasks? We can fix it!
    </h1>
    <p class="sub-text animated fadeInDown">
      No longer waste your time doing things you don't want to worry about, saving you time and money.
    </p>
    <div class="cta animated fadeInDown">
      <%= link_to 'Take a tour', page_path('features'), class: 'button-outline' %>
      <%= link_to 'Sign up', new_user_registration_path, class: 'button' %>
    </div>
    <div class="browsers">
      <%= image_tag 'ss.png', class: 'img-responsive', alt: 'screenshot' %>
    </div>
  </div>		
</div>

<div id="features">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row header">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2>Need an easy way to customize your site?</h2>
        <p>React is perfect for novice developers and experts alike.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row feature">
      <div class="col-md-6 info">
        <h4>You don't need to have great technical experience to use your product.</h4>
        <p>
          Whether you want to fill this paragraph with some text like I'm doing right now, this place
          is perfect to describe some features or anything you want - React has a complete solution for you.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6 image">
        <%= image_tag 'feature1.png', class: 'img-responsive', alt: 'feature1' %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <div class="row feature backwards">
      <div class="col-md-6 info">
        <h4>A fully featured well design template that works.</h4>
        <p>
          You have complete control over the look & feel of your website, we offer the best quality so you
          take your site up and running in no time.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6 image">
        <%= image_tag 'feature2.png', class: 'img-responsive', alt: 'feature2' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>		
</div>

<div id="pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row header">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h3>No contract. Cancel when you want. 30-day money back guarantee.</h3>
        <p>For a limited-time only, get our most popular plan for free. You'll love it!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row charts">
      <% @plans.each do |plan| %>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="chart <%= pricing_table_class plan, @plans %>">
          <% if plan.is_featured? %>
          <div class="popular">Most popular</div>
          <% end %>
          <div class="quantity">
            <span class="dollar">$</span>
            <span class="price"><%= plan.price %></span>
            <span class="period">/<%= plan.interval %></span>
          </div>
          <div class="plan-name"><%= plan.name %></div>
          <div class="specs">
            <div class="spec">
              <%= markdown plan.features.to_s %>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a class="btn-signup button-clear" href="<%= new_user_registration_path %>">
            <% unless plan.has_trial? %>
            <span>Sign up</span>
            <% else %>
            <span>Start free trial</span>
            <% end %>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="slider">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row header">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h3>Easy-to-use dashboard gives you control at your finger tips.</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12 slide-wrapper">
        <div class="slideshow">
          <div class="btn-nav prev"></div>
          <div class="btn-nav next"></div>
          <div class="slide active">
            <%= image_tag 'slider/slide1.png', alt: 'slide1' %>
          </div>
          <div class="slide">
            <%= image_tag 'slider/slide2.png', alt: 'slide2' %>
            <%= image_tag 'slider/slide4.png', alt: 'slide4' %>
          </div>
          <div class="slide">
            <%= image_tag 'slider/slide3.png', alt: 'slide3' %>
          </div>
          <div class="slide">
            <%= image_tag 'slider/slide4.png', alt: 'slide4' %>
          </div>
          <div class="slide">
            <%= image_tag 'slider/slide5.png', alt: 'slide5' %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>	
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="testimonials">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row header">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h3>Trusted by professionals big and small, see what they are saying!</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6">
        <div class="testimonial pull-right">
          <div class="quote">
            I am just quoting some stuff but I am seriously happy about this product. Has a lot of powerful
            features and is so easy to set up, I could stay customizing it day and night, it's just so much fun!
            <div class="arrow-down">
              <div class="arrow"></div>
              <div class="arrow-border"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="author">
            <%= image_tag 'testimonials/testimonial1.jpg', class: 'pic', alt: 'testimonial1' %>
            <div class="name">John McClane</div>
            <div class="company">Microsoft</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-6">
        <div class="testimonial">
          <div class="quote">
            This thing is one of those tools that everybody should be using. I really like it and with this ease to use, you can kickstart your projects and apps and just focus on your business!
            <div class="arrow-down">
              <div class="arrow"></div>
              <div class="arrow-border"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="author">
            <%= image_tag 'testimonials/testimonial2.jpg', class: 'pic', alt: 'testimonial2' %>
            <div class="name">Karen Jones</div>
            <div class="company">Pixar Co.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render 'pages/call_to_action' %>